channel.description:
[ul]Each week there will be a really hard riddle put here! You you can master the riddle you will be put on the list! Don't cheat and don't give up!
[center][b][size=15pt][u]This week's riddle![/u][/size][/b][/center]
1 door closes, 9 open. When 9 close, 1 door opens.
What is it? [hr]
If you know answer. :) If you don't know. :| If your confused. :confused: [hr]
[center][b][u][size=15pt]List[/size][/u][/b][/center] [list][li]Itachi Uchiha[/li] [li]Eh Pretty Easy[/li] [li]io9[/li] [/list]
If you know. Message me answer, I'll put you on the list. Do not post answers here! You'll ruin the fun for all us!
User here got the answer right because: 1. Smart. 2. Read the full thread 3. Had answer and explained* why. (* = Not always needed on each question) [hr]
[center][b][u][size=15pt]Failed List[/size][/u][/b][/center] [list][li]existingqwer[/li] [li]zoltanman[/li] [li]sidishere[/li] [li]The Un-Named[/li] [li]dbzmaster555[/li] [li]Frell[/li] [li]Casey.[/li] [li]Kulkka[/li] [li]exe626[/li] [li]R.I.P RSC[/li] [li]teh spede[/li] [li]nator123123[/li] [li]kloplop321[/li] [li]spankjava[/li] [li]I Am Olan14[/li] [li]MoO[/li] [li].Flair[/li] [li]RXVL[/li] [li]pmgz2[/li] [li]ThAt0n36Uy[/li] [li]Buzzy[/li] [li]Tr3v0r[/li] [/list]

[quote="Casey."]saxaphone[/quote]
None the quote that go up here will be told if they were right or wrong! [hr]
[center][b][size=15pt][u]Riddle Log[/u][/size][/b][/center] [u]June 17 - June 24[/u] [list][li]Three people are at the dinner table. Mom, Dad, and Son. Mom says "What ever your Dad says is False." Dad replys, "Whatever your Mom says is True." [/li][/list] [list][li]The dad was the lier![/li][/list]
[u]June 25 - July 1[/u] [list][li]1 door closes, 9 open. When 9 close, 1 door opens. What is it?" [/li][/list]
Thanks for playing![/ul]

there are 10 doors or chambers if you would. when the water level is at a certain point the one door opens and the other 9 close. this is to regulate the amount of water to make sure you don’t overflow. when the water level gets too high then the one door closes and the other 9 open to get rid of more water. then when the level drops down to the desired level the 9 doors close and the one reopens.

so there you have it. it had me stumped for a while too but there you go!

Your Welcome!

item.description:
@Pwnd wrote:

Are you sure this isn’t googlable?

alrighty guys this is actually pretty easy. the thing the riddle is talking about is a dam. if you dont know how a dam works this is how.

there are 10 doors or chambers if you would. when the water level is at a certain point the one door opens and the other 9 close. this is to regulate the amount of water to make sure you don’t overflow. when the water level gets too high then the one door closes and the other 9 open to get rid of more water. then when the level drops down to the desired level the 9 doors close and the one reopens.

so there you have it. it had me stumped for a while too but there you go!

Your Welcome!
